summary: Kim may try the pomodoro technique recommended by Tim to get more stuff done.

dialogue.speaker: Tim
dialogue.text: Tim: Hi, what's up?

dialogue.speaker: Kim
dialogue.text: Kim: Bad mood tbh, I was going to do lots of stuff but ended up procrastinating

dialogue.speaker: Tim
dialogue.text: Tim: What did you plan on doing?

dialogue.speaker: Kim
dialogue.text: Kim: Oh you know, uni stuff and unfucking my room

dialogue.speaker: Kim
dialogue.text: Kim: Maybe tomorrow I'll move my ass and do everything

dialogue.speaker: Kim
dialogue.text: Kim: We were going to defrost a fridge so instead of shopping I'll eat some defrosted veggies

dialogue.speaker: Tim
dialogue.text: Tim: For doing stuff I recommend Pomodoro technique where u use breaks for doing chores

dialogue.speaker: Tim
dialogue.text: Tim: It really helps

dialogue.speaker: Kim
dialogue.text: Kim: thanks, maybe I'll do that

dialogue.speaker: Tim
dialogue.text: Tim: I also like using post-its in kaban style

summary: Sam is confused, because he overheard Rick complaining about him as a roommate. Naomi thinks Sam should talk to Rick. Sam is not sure what to do.

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: hey  overheard rick say something

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: i don't know what to do :-/

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: what did he say??

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: he was talking on the phone with someone

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: i don't know who

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: and he was telling them that he wasn't very happy here

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: damn!!!

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: he was saying he doesn't like being my roommate

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: wow, how do you feel about it?

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: i thought i was a good rommate

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: and that we have a nice place

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: that's true man!!!

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: i used to love living with you before i moved in with me boyfriend

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: i don't know why he's saying that

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: what should i do???

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: honestly if it's bothering you that much you should talk to him

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: see what's going on

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: i don't want to get in any kind of confrontation though

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: maybe i'll just let it go

dialogue.speaker: Sam
dialogue.text: Sam: and see how it goes in the future

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: it's your choice sam

dialogue.speaker: Naomi
dialogue.text: Naomi: if i were you i would just talk to him and clear the air

summary: Wyatt reminds Neville his wedding anniversary is on the 17th of September. Neville's wife is upset and it might be because Neville forgot about their anniversary.

dialogue.speaker: Neville
dialogue.text: Neville: Hi there, does anyone remember what date I got married on?

dialogue.speaker: Don
dialogue.text: Don: Are you serious?

dialogue.speaker: Neville
dialogue.text: Neville: Dead serious. We're on vacation, and Tina's mad at me about something. I have a strange suspicion that this might have something to do with our wedding anniversary, but I have nowhere to check.

dialogue.speaker: Wyatt
dialogue.text: Wyatt: Hang on, I'll ask my wife.

dialogue.speaker: Don
dialogue.text: Don: Haha, someone's in a lot of trouble :D

dialogue.speaker: Wyatt
dialogue.text: Wyatt: September 17. I hope you remember the year ;)

summary: John didn't show up for class due to some work issues with his boss. Cassandra, his teacher told him which exercises to do, and which chapter to study. They are going to meet up for a beer sometime this week after class.

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: Ave. Was there any homework for tomorrow?

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: hello :D Of course, as always :D

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: What exactly?

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: I'm not sure so I'll check it for you in 20minutes.

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: Cool, thanks. Sorry I couldn't be there, but I was busy as fuck...my stupid boss as always was trying to piss me off

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: No problem, what did he do this time?

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: Nothing special, just the same as always, treating us like children, commanding to do this and that...

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: sorry to hear that. but why don't you just go to your chief and tell him everything?

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: I would, but I don't have any support from others, they are like goddamn pupets and pretend that everything's fine...I'm not gonna fix everything for everyone

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: I understand...Nevertheless, just try to ignore him. I know it might sound ridiculous as fuck, but sometimes there's nothing more you can do.

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: yeah I know...maybe some beer this week?

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: Sure, but I got some time after classes only...this week is gonna be busy

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: no problem, I can drive you home and we can go to some bar or whatever.

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: cool. ok, I got this homework. it's page 15 ex. 2 and 3, I also asked the others to study another chapter, especially the vocabulary from the very first pages. Just read it.

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: gosh...I don't know if I'm smart enough to do it :'D

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: you are, don't worry :P Just circle all the words you don't know and we'll continue on Monday.

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: ok...then I'll try my best :D

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: sure, if you will have any questions just either text or call me and I'll help you.

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: I hope I won't have to waste your time xD

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: you're not wasting my time, I'm your teacher, I'm here to help. This is what I get money for, also :P

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: just kidding :D ok, so i guess we'll stay in touch then

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: sure, have a nice evening :D

dialogue.speaker: John
dialogue.text: John: you too, se ya

dialogue.speaker: Cassandra
dialogue.text: Cassandra: Byeeeee

summary: Sarah sends James an instrumental song he might like. James knows the song. The brain connects the songs to the context they were played in and brings to mind the associated memories.

dialogue.speaker: Sarah
dialogue.text: Sarah: I found a song on youtube and I think you'll like it

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: What song?

dialogue.speaker: Sarah
dialogue.text: Sarah: <file_other>

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: Oh. I know it!

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: I heard it before in some compilation

dialogue.speaker: Sarah
dialogue.text: Sarah: I can't stop playing it over and over

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: That's exactly how I know lyrics to all of the songs on my playlist :D

dialogue.speaker: Sarah
dialogue.text: Sarah: Haha. No lyrics here though. Instrumental ;D

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: Instrumental songs are different kind of music.

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: But you have to remember that the activity you do when you listen to this song

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: Is the actvity your brain will connect to the song

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: And everytime you play this song at home

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: You'll be thinking of your work

dialogue.speaker: Sarah
dialogue.text: Sarah: Yeah, I know that. That's why we sometimes say - I used to like that song, but now it just reminds me of bad memories

dialogue.speaker: James
dialogue.text: James: Yup. Everytime you change your partner, you have to get rid of your favorite music :D

dialogue.speaker: Sarah
dialogue.text: Sarah: Hahaha. True, true.

summary: Matt invites Agnes for a date to get to know each other better. They'll go to the Georgian restaurant in Kazimierz on Saturday at 6 pm, and he'll pick her up on the way to the place.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: Do you want to go for date?

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: Wow! You caught me out with this question Matt.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: Why?

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: I simply didn't expect this from you.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: Well, expect the unexpected.

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: Can I think about it?

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: What is there to think about?

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: Well, I don't really know you.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: This is the perfect time to get to know eachother

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: Well that's true.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: So let's go to the Georgian restaurant in Kazimierz.

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: Now your convincing me.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: Cool, saturday at 6pm?

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: That's fine.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: I can pick you up on the way to the restaurant.

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: That's really kind of you.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: No problem.

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: See you on saturday.

dialogue.speaker: Matt
dialogue.text: Matt: Yes, looking forward to it.

dialogue.speaker: Agnes
dialogue.text: Agnes: Me too.
